It is said, we have lately got a new state officer, called, The minister of the house of commons, which, being interpreted signifies, I suppose, the Nose-leader, of that august assembly. It is always to be understood, that I mean no reflection upon the present times, which are always immaculate, while they are present. But we have in the LOND. MAG. 1767, an account of this officer, as follows;
The marquis next proposed Mr. C—nw—y for secretary of state, and minister of the house of commons.
